My husband and I made this the other night, served it over couscous and absolutely LOVED it!!! We cut the recipe in half since it's just the two of us and we wished we hadn't so we could have had more leftovers to enjoy. After reading the reviews we did change it up a bit . For the halved recipe, we used 1 lemon in total - we thinly sliced half of it and cut out all the pith, but still added the zest. We then added one slightly thicker slice, pith and all, and the juice of the other half (a little less than a tablespoon). We used chicken broth instead of the water and doubled all the spices except for the cayenne. Make sure you salt the chicken before you add it, we forgot and added about a 1/2 teaspoon before simmering and we still had to salt it quite a bit on the plate. We served the mint on the side so we could add it to our own tastes - my husband liked a little, I liked a lot. Don't omit anything - the complexities of the flavors are just right! We actually found ourselves excited the next day in anticipation of eating the leftovers. This one is a keeper for sure!!

Rating: 4
This is great! A really fabulous flavour. The trick to not having any bitterness - is NOT to exclude the lemon or decrease the amount, but make sure you cut off as much of the pith (that white stuff between the skin and the lemon flesh) as you can. So, that will possibly mean - depending on the lemons you have - cutting the rind off first and slicing that up, then dicarding the pith and cutting up the lemon. It truly is worth the while. YUMMM.... I'm definately making this one again...

