Rating: 3
I didn't make this exactly per the recipe, so that might explain why I give it 3 forks, unlike some others who have not rated it as well. I pretty much used the recipe as a guide for the spices, and even then I increased the amounts based on feedback here. But basically I first browned the chicken, removed it, then sauteed some onions/shallots/garlic until golden, then deglazed it with some chicken stock (~half can) and added in the spices. I cooked it until most of the liquid was gone, then added the chicken back and the remainder of the stock, and also threw in the lemon slices (1 lemon) and some cilantro stems. Simmered for a little bit, then added in the chickpeas. Unfortunately there was a little too much liquid so I had to simmer for longer than anticipated, which resulted in slightly softer chickpeas (although not mushy). Towards the end, I added some baby carrots and some raisins, and then topped it off with some chopped cilantro. Overall, the flavour was quite good, and I would say the only real flaw was slightly overdone chickpeas. I had intended on adding some crushed tomatoes, but there was already too much liquid so I omitted that. The carrots and raisins also added another nice layer of flavour (a little sweet from the raisins) and texture (a little crisp from the carrots). This was a good example of why I always read through the reviews before trying the recipe out. Just looking at the recipe, I wouldn't have guessed that it might come out underspiced or over-tangy (from the lemon). I always try to read all the reviews, and if there seem to be a disproportionately large number of similar comments, I'll heed the warning.

