Rating: 4
This dish was *fantastic*! Per previous reviews, I cut the lemon in 1/8's so I could fish it out before serving -- no bitter taste at all! Also, I browned the chicken first, and doubled the minced ginger and all the dried spices. My only comment is that the carrots need to be cut a little smaller to cook in 10 minutes. Served it with Israeli (pearl) couscous. Definitely will make this again and again!

Rating: 3
This recipe was great....I browned the chicken as one of the cooks suggested....and added quartered fennel, turkish apricots and whole dried figs as suggested by another tagine recipe on epicurious.com. But I also strongly agree with the cook who advised to be careful of the lemon. For us, it was too strong to use fresh lemon....we felt it put the earthy Moroccan flavors way out of balance. So we will make it again, but without the lemon. Overall a good recipe. We made it in the morning, left it to simmer on the stove, went out for an afternoon ski, came back to a great dinner.

