Rating: 4
I absolutely loved this recipe, in its original form. I decided, when on a health kick to try it a second time -- omitting the chicken, and adding vegetable broth and more veggies to turn it into a super-healthy thick & hearty soup (more like an exotic stew). It has since become my favorite meal, and everyone I have ever served it too loves it as well. I double the recipe, omit the chicken, and add: 1 potato (or parsnip or sweet potato) cubed; some chopped spinach or collard greens; 2 cans vegetable broth; more water to desired consistency; more carrots to liking; 2 fresh tomatoes chopped, and whatever other veggies you think would be good -- but keep the carbs down,it really doesn't need it. It's absolutely delicious! I serve it with just some crusty whole grain baguette w/ butter. Maybe a little parmesan or white cheddar grated on top. It is soooo satisfying (and healthy to boot!)!!! Once you double the original recipe & turn it into a soup/stew following the above, it feeds 2 people for an entire week. For variations during the week to avoid getting tired of it, I've had the following on the side to mix in on different days of the week: cous-cous, barley, wild rice, and/or chicken (sauteed with just enough of the spice mixture to give it some flavor stand-alone: coriander, cinnamon, cayenne, paprika, onion powder). Yummmmmmmm.............

